{
  "id": "guide/component-store/install",
  "title": "Installation",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/component-store/install.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"installation\">Installation<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component-store/install#installation\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-npm\">Installing with <code>npm</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component-store/install#installing-with-npm\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>For more information on using <code>npm</code> check out the docs <a href=\"https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nnpm install @ngrx/component-store --save\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-yarn\">Installing with <code>yarn</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component-store/install#installing-with-yarn\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>For more information on using <code>yarn</code> check out the docs <a href=\"https://yarnpkg.com/getting-started/usage#installing-all-the-dependencies\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nyarn add @ngrx/component-store\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-ng-add\">Installing with <code>ng add</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/component-store/install#installing-with-ng-add\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>If your project is using the Angular CLI 6+ then you can install the ComponentStore to your project with the following <code>ng add</code> command <a href=\"https://angular.io/cli/add\" target=\"_blank\">(details here)</a>:</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nng add @ngrx/component-store@latest\n</code-example>\n<p>This command will automate the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Update <code>package.json</code> > <code>dependencies</code> with <code>@ngrx/component-store</code>.</li>\n<li>Run the package manager to install the added dependency. </li>\n</ol>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - guide/component-store\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - guide/component-store/install#installation\n - guide/component-store/install#installing-with-ng-add\n - guide/component-store/install#installing-with-npm\n - guide/component-store/install#installing-with-yarn\n - https://angular.io/cli/add\n - https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/component-store/install.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n - https://yarnpkg.com/getting-started/usage#installing-all-the-dependencies\n-->"
}